{"parentUuid":"d6435150-6bdd-452b-91b0-45dc911ef6aa","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"8f69e5ec-0fb1-4d88-a778-e67e3b28d043","version":"2.0.42","gitBranch":"","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_01LUZrkgWqyVY7vWxjJg4HqV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah, lovely! So datawizz.ai is apparently living its best life behind Cloudflare's protective embrace. Let me break down this DNS treasure trove for you:\n\n## **A Records (IPv4 addresses)**\n- `172.67.158.37`\n- `104.21.14.67`\n\nThese are Cloudflare proxy IPs. So the website is hiding behind Cloudflare like a shy developer behind their laptop at a networking event. When you visit datawizz.ai, you're actually hitting Cloudflare's servers first.\n\n## **AAAA Records (IPv6 addresses)**\n- `2606:4700:3036::6815:e43`\n- `2606:4700:3033::ac43:9e25`\n\nThe fancy IPv6 version of the above. Because apparently 340 undecillion addresses is *barely* enough for the internet.\n\n## **MX Records (Mail servers)**\nThey're using Google Workspace for email (shocking, I know):\n- Priority 1: `aspmx.l.google.com` (main mail server)\n- Priority 5: `alt1.aspmx.l.google.com` and `alt2.aspmx.l.google.com` (backup servers)\n- Priority 10: `alt3.aspmx.l.google.com` and `alt4.aspmx.l.google.com` (more backups)\n\nLower priority numbers = \"check me first!\" So they've got a whole backup brigade in case Google's main mail server decides to take a coffee break.\n\n## **TXT Records**\n- `google-site-verification=HNs-M8XQYV_wbcSLABJ65iH9761kmeMto0N5ytd_M08` - Proving to Google \"yes, we own this domain, we promise!\"\n- `v=spf1 include:dc-aa8e722993._spfm.datawizz.ai ~all` - SPF record that says \"only these servers can send email on our behalf, everyone else is sus\"\n\n## **NS Records (Name servers)**\n- `bart.ns.cloudflare.com`\n- `lia.ns.cloudflare.com`\n\nCloudflare is handling their DNS. At this point, I'm starting to think Cloudflare is basically their entire infrastructure team.\n\n**TL;DR:** datawizz.ai is using Cloudflare for hosting/CDN/DNS, Google for email, and has proper email authentication set up. It's a pretty standard modern web setup - nothing too fancy, nothing too sketchy!"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":969,"cache_read_input_tokens":15718,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":969,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":614,"service_tier":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CVrL2kx2iRmRjGN1PWmyH","type":"assistant","uuid":"11edc474-4667-40d1-b1d7-4fc35b2bfaec","timestamp":"2025-12-06T23:49:42.455Z"}
